content: There are no meaningful changes to the room. This is not the normally used smots footage, however, it does a short climb jump off the little ledge when entering the room to the right, and skips the second spring by dashing upwards instead of left and lands on the 4th spring from the 3rd spring.
The modern, more commonly used footage of smots-8. The original.
Still nothing changed. Madeline dashed into the block instead of holding it, and at the last part she neutral jumped on the second last block so it didn't fall.
The same normal smots-8 footage except the dash into the third spring twice, and after the two up dashes at the end, she does an upright to get to smots-9.

Completely normal smots-8 footage, except instead of hitting the first spring it dashes upwards and does a spiked corner jump off of the top left of the first floating moonblock after the spring it missed, grabbing onto the 2nd spring's platform and climbing up and continuing as normal.

In this episode it enters smots-8 and does a downleft dash, right dash, up dash, then a down or a downleft it is hard to tell. The room continues as normal until the end when instead of doing the second updash to go to smots-9 it stays on the block and goes under the spinners to smots-9.
Normal smots-8 footage, except at the end where it performs a reverse hyper into a demodash to go through the spinners at the end, instead of the normal 2 updashes.

Upon entering smots-8 it does a reverse wavedash into a right dash which was meant to be a coost but failed. It does a reverse hyper instead of a normal hyper to get to the first spring, and then do a downleft onto the first spring. At the end it struggles to climb the first falling block and when it gets to the top of the second it does an upright above the spinners to smots-9.

This episode is normal smots gaming footage except the 3rd spring was hit twice, a right dash instead of upright through the spinners, and it ran out of stamina while climbing the last two blocks and dashed upright into smots-9 instead of updashes.
Normal smots-8 footage, except at the end where they grab onto the falling block and perform a climb jump after the block has fallen, going under the spinners with a right dash at the end.

In this episode it enters smots-8 and does a left dash at the beginning. The room continues as normal until it does a big climbjump to skip doing the first updash on the smaller falling platform and just does the second updash, which is now the only updash, on the bigger block and makes it to smots-9.

This episode is the first to feature a major change to smots-8. Upon entering the room there is the "sandwich" lava that starts in hot mode and only the ceiling part of the lava can be seen due to it being pushed far downwards. The lava starts rising up but it turns out everytime it dashes, the lava changes mode from hot to cold and starts going downwards and vice versa. This causes the need for stalling and some strat changes to stay above or below the lava.
Normal gameplay, until after they hit the last spring where they demo through the second to last wall of spinners.

Smots-8, but there is a seeded strawberry consisting of six seeds scattered across the room that they collect, spawning a strawberry at the final falling platform. The seeds are:
On the left of the block the first spring is connected to.
On the left of first moonblock in the room.
On the spiked moonblock under the second spring.
On the left of the block the 5th spring is attached to.
On the first of the 2 Moonblocks next to each other on the bottom left of the ceiling foreground tiles.
On the left of the 7th spring.

Here, it performs a couple spikes jumps on the spiked left walls of the first few moon blocks of smots-8 after skipping the first spring entirely with an upright. They let the ending block fall down and go under the spinners. Other then that, the room is the same.

The player performs a spiked corner jump on the top right corner of the block with the first spring, to which it then performs several spike jumps/neutrals on the side of the next few platforms' spikes before the second spring, even dashing upright to jump on more spikes. Additionally, not only do they hit the 8th spring twice, but on the first block after the fifth spring, it demos between that block and the ceiling. Then, it performs a demo after hitting the last spring on the second to last wall of spinners, and finally it does a reverse hyper into a demo to go through the last wall.

This episode is in a 16:16 format with black borders on the top and bottom to look like 16:9, and every 4 seconds it transitions to a new frame of smots-8 gameplay with a stock transition effect you would find in a video editor, with the first frame being entering smots-8, progressing further into the room each frame. In the background the song "The Penis (Eek!)" is playing, and the video quality is very bad.
Normal smots-8, but Madeline has a dash trail the entire time.

This is normal smots gaming smots-8 footage until passing the 6th spring exactly 14 seconds in when smots gaming suddenly reveals that it has the "extra jumps" extended variant set to infinite, and instead of dashing to the 7th spring it jumps to it and then continues the room as normal.
This is entirely normal smots-8 footage (apart from the last updash now being a jump and an upleft) but the entire time the "mirror mode" variant is on.
This is normal smots-8 footage, except the vanilla variant "Other Self" is turned on which turns your player skin into badeline.

This is completely normal smots-8 footage except there is no freeze frames at all, and at the end it dashs up right to land on the falling platforms instead of climbing them and then when it reaches the top it performs the signature two updashes.
It's normal smots-8 footage except at 12 seconds a single snowball flies across the screen.
This gameplay in this episode is unchanged. However, this episode was the first episode of smots gaming that premiered on YouTube.
Smots-8 footage, but with low gravity.

The first time of many Twitch streamer, hardlist map clearer, hard goldener, YouTuber "Parrot Dash" is shown in smots gaming. This episode is Parrot's 3rd entry in smots-8, the video only shows her playing through smots-8. Smots-8 is still named minigame instead of smots gaming, and smots-9 is still named "Im straight" instead of Piano.
Normal smots-8 gameplay, except that right before Madeline dashes, it cuts to when that same dash ends. This applies for every dash Madeline is supposed to perform in the room.
It's smots-8 but three badeline clones chase madeline throught the whole level. They also start to appear in smots-9 but the video gets cut off.
The playthrough of smots-8 is normal until the very end, when the big falling block falls upwards and crushes Madeline.
This is smots-8 completed while bringing a jellyfish to the end, letting Madeline skip most of the obstacles in the room.

This episode starts with the game being unpaused after turning the "Always in Feather" extended variant on while holding onto the wall in smots-7. It enters smots-8 and does some cool tricks until hitting the 8th spring and getting back into a feather after that and entering smots-9 after flying around.
Smots-8 but there are badeline bosses throughout the room that push madeline back when hit, this allows for skips or setbacks/time losses throughout the room.
It's smots-8 but all of the sufaces are bouncy, springing away Madeline when she touches them. Aswell the edges of the screen are bouncy too if they don't have a transition, like smots-9.
This episode is completely normal smots-8 footage. It even uses the classic footage with the two up-dashes, the most commonly used on the channel. Except: the entire video is played in reverse.
When entering smots-8, darkness is turned on and all of the tiles, spinners, and springs turn black. The background remains unchanged, making the gameplay still visible.

This is a normal clear of smots-8, except at the 16 second mark, the popular video of a man saying "I love undertime slopper" appears on screen and plays, although "undertime slopper" is dubbed over with a TTS voice and replaced with "smots gaming".

This is a "Where's Waldo?" picture, but instead of waldo it says "Where's smots?". Slightly above and to the right of the middle of the screen, there is very small footage of smots-8. This recording does not do the two updashes, but rather jumps on the second block and does an upright dash. It also dashes back into the second spring to hit it twice.

This is the meme where people would take the Good Day Peach Soju alcoholic beverage and have the top part say "This tastes like juice" the middle part say "Im not drunk yet" and the base middle part say something completely different, such as good girl/boy juice as the name of the drink and the base saying "Meow meow meow :333 meow :3 mrow purrrr :3 purmrow meow :3 :3 meoowwww :3 mewmew", except in this episode the base is just a smots-8 video with audio.
It's just smots-8 with a greyscale filter on

It's smots-8 but the wind dies down immediately and because of that it needs to have invincibility on to clear the room due to not being able to reach spring 6 from the moon blocks and a wall of spinners blocking it after spring 8 and not being able to reach the falling platforms.

This is smots-8 completed while bringing a Theo crystal to the end, making the room much harder with some different moves rather than the normal strats. Smots-7 is not visible in the video, as it starts at the spawn point of smots-8. A respawning noise is audible at the very beginning. The video ends before the first platform of smots-9 is reached.

This episode is a Google Slideshow with the first slide saying "smots tutorial" and the subtitle saying "By smots gaming". Each slide after is various frames from gameplay of smots-8, each one progressing farther and farther through the room, ending on a frame before the dash to the block in smots-9. Additionally, every slide has the transition "flip" at 2.5 seconds.

This episode is structured similarly to Strawberry Jam's Grandmaster Heartside map. Each room from the original is seen in the form of smots-8, styled to look like its corresponding room from the Heartside. These rooms also use the original map's mechanics from each of the Heartside's room. The death towards the end in flag 3 is a reference to the map that the Heartside's room is based off of, Lava Layer, where in certain spots of that map, an invisible kaizo block is placed in a cheeky attempt obstruct your path.

It's a normal playthrough of smots gaming, but starting a few frames before the first extended hyper at the start, the playthrough slows down by 1000x. This means that the rest of the playthrough runs for about 1 frame every 16 to 17 seconds, making it the longest smots gaming video to date with a total length of 7 hours, 46 minutes and 9 seconds.
It's a normal playthrough of smots-5
This is smots gaming's official apology for posting the wrong room the episode before (smots-5).
This episode is a bunch of minecraft survival gameplay, except many of the blocks have been retextured to frames of smots-8.

The video starts with the Daily Dose of Celeste intro, but instead of Celeste they say smots gaming, followed by smots-8. Instead of the usual smots-8, upon reaching the second spring they dash right into it 9 times before continuing. They trigger the falling block early, and crouch on it before falling to their death.
It's smots-8 but the whole level is filled with debris particles which move out of the way when madeline gets close to them, essentialy drawing the path that madeline takes.

This episode is normal smots-8 footage except all the foreground tiles and moonblocks and falling blocks are now invisible like in 5d, revealing the background tiles underneath, and it dies instead of dashing to the smots-9 block, or because the smots-9 block doesn't exist.
It's a playthrough of the game "Spelunky", but the player is smots-8.
This episode is a jigsaw puzzle of 16 pieces that form one of the first frames of smots-8. Then footage of smots-8 starts playing in the full picture formed by the pieces.
This is smots-8 recreated in the game Ultimate Chicken Horse. It is built basically the same except springs don't push you that far horizontally so there is a platform under each spring.

An image of a word search with smots-8 wind ambience in the background. After 3 minutes of searching, they find "smotsgaming" in the word search, starting in the top left corner and going down diagonally.
Normal smots-8 footage but starting 2 seconds in the "Audio Jungle" watermark audio plays every 5 seconds.

This is the meme picture from 2009 where Joe Biden has a speech bubble that says "OKAY SMOT GUY!!! LET'S SEE **YOU** TAKE A CRACK AT IT!!!" while yelling across a table at someone, while the table has a 2 piece puzzle of a smiling face. In this episode smot guy is replaced with smart guy (this might be because the meme picture was recaptioned to say smart in 2020), and the puzzle pieces are just smots-8 footage.

For 8 days from episode 105-113 (skipping day 111), smots gaming uploaded a day of "smots week" where it would show itself playing through smots-8 but in some different way each time. This is day 1. It plays smots-8 the usual way.

For 8 days from episode 105-113 (skipping day 111), smots gaming uploaded a day of "smots week" where it would show itself playing through smots-8 but in some different way each time. This is day 2. It plays smots-8 normally until it does a right dash instead of an upright dash to get from spring 6 to spring 7. Then it skips the second updash and instead does an upright to get into smots-9.

For 8 days from episode 105-113 (skipping day 111), smots gaming uploaded a day of "smots week" where it would show itself playing through smots-8 but in some different way each time. This is day 3. It plays smots-8 like normal, until the very end where it skips the 2 updashes and just does an upright into smots-9.

For 8 days from episode 105-113 (skipping day 111), smots gaming uploaded a day of "smots week" where it would show itself playing through smots-8 but in some different way each time. This is day 4. It does the exact same thing as smots week day 3, (episode 107) but does the upright at the end a lot faster.

For 8 days from episode 105-113 (skipping day 111), smots gaming uploaded a day of "smots week" where it would show itself playing through smots-8 but in some different way each time. This is day 5. It is literally the exact same as smots week day 4 (episode 108).

For 8 days from episode 105-113 (skipping day 111), smots gaming uploaded a day of "smots week" where it would show itself playing through smots-8 but in some different way each time. This is day 6. It is normal smots-8 footage until doing a rightdash instead of upright from springs 6 to 7. Then it skips the first of the two updashes and falls down to go under the spinners into smots-9.
This episode not only interupts day 7 of smots week, but also starts as if it was about to show the last showcase on a Nintendo Direct, but when they roll the clip it is just smots-8.

For 8 days from episode 105-113 (skipping day 111), smots gaming uploaded a day of "smots week" where it would show itself playing through smots-8 but in some different way each time. This is day 7. Normal smots-8 footage until rightdash instead of upright to get to spring 7 after spring 6. Then it skips both updashes and do a quick upright into smots-9.

For 8 days from episode 105-113 (skipping day 111), smots gaming uploaded a day of "smots week" where it would show itself playing through smots-8 but in some different way each time. This is day.. 8? Anyways it does normal smots-8 until the very end where it skips both up dashes and goes under the spinners.

Smots 8 gameplay as normal, but edited to look like a very old film playing, as it has vertical lines appearing and dissapearing, the audio is in poor quality, thick horizontal black lines at the top and bottom for the aspec ratio, the screen is shaking randomly and wildly, and the  screen pulses sometimes.
In first few seconds, a text to speech reads: "Madeline tried to play smots-8. You won't believe what happened next!" Then, at the end of the screen, it shows the car crash green screen.
It's a playthrough of hollow knight except the knight is replaced with a looping video of smots-8 <:smotsgaming:1326331682156056638>

That meme where people would take random things and try to make them look like the "Bad Apple" (A song that was originally background music for a level in Touhou Gensokyo ~ Lotus Land Story, but remixed for an album, with added lyrics, getting a music video made of it.) music video due to the music video only having black and white colors. In this episode of smots gaming, the colors seem to have been removed from smots-8, with the Bad Apple music video playing in the background. When the music video has a white part in the background, the tilesets, background decals, spinners, wind, and Madeline are all black and vice versa when the background is black. Details in Madeline, the tilesets, the spinners, and the background decals are sometimes contradicting this though to make it not just look like a silhouette. The wind also changes things, as when it is on Madeline while she is on a white background, the wind particles will be white due to being on a black Madeline.

It's a playthrough of smots 8 with a livesplit timer in the bottom right with splits for all of the springs, the falling blocks and the room transition. The category is SMotS-8 and the game is final goodbye.

This episode is a game of Balatro, except the very first joker it gets is a smots gaming joker that is just a smots-8 gif, which triggers every card played, saying smots gaming, except it does absolutely nothing and is just there.
This is a picture of the SMOTS segment golden in tier 4 of the top golden list, but the text "Scattered Mirror of the Storm" is replaced with footage of smots-8.
Before the second spring in smots-8, a short pause then a fake YouTube ad with smots-5 pops up. It is skipped and (after a shorter pause) the rest of smots-8 continues.

This episode starts off with Madeline climbing into smots-8, just as normal, but as she is about to hyper, a dialogue cutscene starts where she says:
"You know what"
"Not feeling it today"
She then dashes back to the platform that leads into smots-8, crouches on it, and falls through it back into smots-7. Travelling backwards through a platform of this nature is not possible in vanilla Celeste without a Feather.

This episode has smots-8 gameplay in the background, while in the foreground is a game of mobile NYT Games Wordle.
The first word guessed is "block" with all letters gray except the middle o. ⬛⬛🟩⬛⬛
The second word it used was "dashs" with the middle s being yellow and the last s being green. ⬛⬛🟨⬛🟩
The third word was "spike", only the first s was green. 🟩⬛⬛⬛⬛
The 4th word was "boing" the second spot being o was yellow. ⬛🟨⬛⬛⬛
On the fifth guess it used "smots" and all were green. 🟩🟩🟩🟩🟩

What the.. This is.. Smots Week day 9? Welp, I guess we doin 9 day weeks now. Anyway, for smots week day 9, it goes through smots-8 entirely normally until the end when it dashes onto the first falling block and jumps on to the second, to dash upright into smots-9.

This episode is normal smots-8 but every single action is narrated by tiktok tts. For example: they right dash and it says "right dash" same with up demo, climb jump, extended hyper, etc. It then ends with a tiktok watermark ending except it doesnt say anything for the name.

The episode begins in the Super Mario Galaxy 2 map screen where the player selects supermassive galaxy. Upon going in to the level it's a scaled up version of smots-8 with really low gravity and long dashes which it proceeds to play through.

This episode is the meme from early to mid 2023 where there was a looping cat moving back and fourth with the song "Dubidubidu" by Christell's chorus playing, singing "chipi chipi chapa chapa dubi dubi daba daba magico mi dubi dubi boom boom boom boom", except this time the background is replaced with smots-8 audio and gameplay.
This is gameplay of the game Rabbit and Steel. The main character is replaced by smots-8, each frame of the Celeste gameplay corresponding to a different sprite animation.

Smots-8 footage is now a desmos recreation with the circles being the spinners,  brown rectangles are springs, dark blue rectangles are spikes, black rectangles are moon blocks, and the color changing rectangle is Madeline hitbox with the corresponding hair color depending on how many dashes left.
It's normal smots gaming footage except the colors are inverted, it's flipped horizontally and vertically, and it's playing backwards.

That iconic scene from the first Minecraft movie trailer where Jack Black says "I... am STEVE" but cut off after he says "I... am S" and starts playing the smots-8 gif on top of him. The video ends before smots gaming even starts falling past the center of the room vertically after entering smots-9 through the very top right because it skipped the 2 updashes and instead did an upright right at the end.
footage of smots-8 except it is being eaten, a chomp sound effect plays during every bite

Oops! Lyra accidentally uploaded the Daily Dose of Celeste video for that day where parrot_dash dies in smots-9 after showing all of smots-8 instead of showing the smots gaming video for that day!
The clips shown in the ddoc video were:
-Parrot getting through the middle of smots-7, through the entirety of smots-8, and dying in smots-9 to a delayed jump whilst trying to wavedash, causing her to not get any speed, and fall to her death.
-A submission from BUGFlower413 about thier new and upcoming map: Demoness!DAMARA MEGIDO
-eg_vr's submission of their joke map, 5c with 56 Seekers
-That is all. Thanks for watching!

This is Parrot's smots-8 playthrough with the platinum berry. After smots-8, she misses a wavedash and dies in smots-9. Throughout the video, there are short flashes of the moment when she fails in smots-9, as a reference to the "subtle foreshadowing" meme.
smots-8, but gay

This is a clip of Parrot Dash (29/10/2024), she enters smots-8 with 9D's Platinum Berry and clear the room, when she enters smots-9, she does a dash miss timed. She put herself back on the block she wanted to wavedash on and pause the game, grab her water bottle. At this moment, the clip is edited, the game returns to map while she's breathing getting ready to try and save herself.

Here, they type into ChatGPT: "Hello, I came across a body in the river. I need help. do I call the cops? what do I do? I'm scared. The worst part is. I recognize it. I recognize... him. Seven years ago. It was my fault. How could he be back? His face... Unchanged. Like it happened an hour ago. The blood in the same places. What do I do?". Then, ChatGPT responds: "smots gaming". For the whole video, it plays the wind sound effect from Celeste.

In this episode it makes a tierlist of all the smots rooms. This is the result:
Tier S: smots-8
Tier A: smots-2, 3, 4, 6, 7, 9-15
Tier B: smots-16-29
Tier C: Every room from the 2.5k section of smots
Tier D: smots-5

In this episode, it shows that one video with the original caption, "97 year old NYC diner still serves their Coke the old-fashioned way." but Coke is replaced with smots, and the thing they are using to make the Coke is covered with a smots-8 room video.

Normal smots gaming smots-8 footage until 7 seconds in when the DuckTales (NES) OST - The Moon Theme starts playing and at 10 seconds when smots gaming dashes up to the 5th spring, it suddenly has a really slow but infinite dash that last forever, eventually ending with it off screen.
It's normal footage of smots-8 except the audio keeps shifting from your left ear to your right ear at various speeds every time it hits a spring.

This episode starts with a light blue screen, the song playing in the background is "sneaky snitch" by Kevin MacLeod, with text on screen saying "top 10 smots" it then goes down the line of top 10 smots and each time it says "number #" the text is always doing something different, for number 2 it wasnt even there. Each clip it shows for top 10 smots is the exact same, the ending of smots-7, the normal footage of smots-8, and ending in smots-9. The last clip ends with "Thanks for watching" and ends.

This episodes starts with a normal clear of smots-8, though there is a wallbounce done after the first spring, which isn't typical. Near the end of the clear, the video fades into an IRL video of a computer screen, with smots-8 being currently played. It slowly zooms out. Youtuber GD Colon's plushie is seen to the right of the screen, and a second monitor is seen to the left, with wallpaper from the game Rhythm Doctor. As the video finished zooming out, The same Youtuber is holding a controller, and finishes beating smots-8. He then turns around and says "Hi, it's me, smots gaming. You might know me from my second channel, GD Colon. I just wanted to thank you so much for enjoying my smots gaming content, and I can guarantee you we've got lots more hilarious smots on the way."
It's a clip from the beginning of the second minecraft movie trailer where Jack Black is mining and when he would normally go into minecraft, it's smots-8. as a smots, i yearned for the gaming
The video shows a monster singing in the mobile game "My Singing Monsters". However, the audio is replaced with wind audio from smots-8. The player name is "Smots Gaming".
im gonna fuckin smots

The episode starts on the title screen then it makes a new save file named smots gaming. After that it plays through all of prologue, skipping the granny cutscene. In city it plays the first room which is unchanged however the second room is smots-8 decorated like forsaken city. After playing through it, it dashes into the third room which is smots-9, also decorated like city, and then the video cuts off in the usual smots gaming fashion.

It starts out in the starting room of The Legened of Zelda for the NES, notably there is an input display in the bottom left. It walks into the cave where you get your starting sword, but the sword is a video of smots-8 where it lets it play through and the video ends.

The video features the start of a new playthrough of Super Mario Bros. 3. In stage 1-3, Mario enters the background of the level, leading to a chest room. He is told by a toad that "One toot on this whistle will send you to a far away land!". The chest opens and smots-8 as a video pops out of it, likely meaning the "far away land" actually referred to smots-8. The video continues to take up the entire screen and play out until the end.

In this episode it plays through smots-8 but when it gets to the second falling block, it disapears revealing another smots-8 behind it which it plays through. Through out the whole room there are ingredients and instructions for a cookie recipe which it pauses to read. In total there are 8 instructions, probably a refrence to smots-**8**, with the final one saying "Enjoy your smots-8 themed cookies! Store the remaining cookies in a container for no more than a few days". When it goes into smots-9 it says "Tell us down in the comments if you followed along at home!" 🍪
the video starts with the joker reveal trailer from smash bros, but when the invitation is flipped, it instead shows smots-8!

This is footage from The Game Awards 2024, right before the premiere of "Intergalactic: The Heretic Prophet". The start of the premiere is a quote, "smots gaming" - smots gaming, 2024. After this is footage of a space landscape with asteroids, and some of the asteroids are replaced with smots-8. The video ends before the premiere is over.

Many people have pointed out the FPS counter in the corner of my videos, and have tried to figure out some deeper meaning from it. In order to feed this theory even more, I made a video where the FPS counter ominously ticks down in a timer-like manner, and included one of my favorite game OST songs along with some visual effects for theatrical flair. Once the timer reaches 0, the video returns to smots-8 to finish the clip.
### \- smots gaming <:verified:1327799187433193513>
The secret 26th golden in the 2024 golden advent calendar is the critically acclaimed room smots-8.

This episode starts off with the role information screen of a game of Among Us. Like a normal Among Us game, the players spawn in and begin walking off to do their tasks. The player character is named pink, and all the other players are also named colours corresponding to their player colour. After walking to medbay and opening a task menu, an emergency meeting is called. All players say "smots gaming" in chat except for red, who says "what are you talking about?". All other players immediately vote red off, causing them to be ejected. However, they are ejected into footage of smots-8, instead of the normal space background.
Time slows down as Madeline charges up her speed, and she finished the room in less than 1 second, seemingly a refernce to The Flash.

I wanna Atone the Flower room 13 in smots-8 style. On attempt 247 Madeline beats the room and get teleported to smots-9. This is also how many times a player named issy or mystral fox got to the last jump before beating the room.

Instead of the room, there is a desert seeker from the map 5b funny version by ninz, carrying Madeline and tell her fun facts. Here are all the fun facts the desert seeker said: "smots-8's room dimensions are 200x23", "There are 8 springs in smots-8. Coincidence?", "The desert seeker is from 5b funny version by ninz", "The "rightstrong" wind in the room option is different from the "rightstrong" wind trigger.", "There are 240 foreground tiles in smots-8", "smots gaming is run by [the video is cut off]",
The user opens Firefox and googles "how to pronounce smots". when pronounce is clicked, it plays the wind from smots-8, but when played slow it plays the full smots-8 audio

This episode is an IRL video, There are baked christmas cookies with all kinds of different frosting designs and shapes. (while some of them are hard to see, the ones we were able to recognize will be listed here in order of apparition: a red candy cane, a white butterfly, a white character with a brown mustache, blue eyes and a yellow crown, an unfrosted candy cane, a yellow and orange bell, an unfrosted arrow tip, a white gingerbread man, two ice cream cones, a blue dino, a blue snowflake, a blue kite, a blue gingerbread man, a mountain? (maybe celeste mountain?), 3 blue butterflies, an orange butterfly, another gingerbread character (this one kinda reminds me of freddy), a giant faceless ginerbread person, a green butterfly and one last blue and red guy. There are also a lot of stars, trees, boots and flowers that I didn't want to name because there are way too many of them) On the last rack there is a smots-8 star-shaped cookie and a flamingo cookie, as the camera pans past all the cookies, and Undertale's "Uwa, so holiday!" plays. It suddenly reverses and slowly zooms into the smots cookie, then switches to the flamingo cookie. The video then transitions into a slide showing pictures of flamingos with the text saying "Happy international flamingo day!", while [a variation of the same song](https://youtu.be/HBfUVatdNJ8?si=NtbjFcVv-aaxLmzq) plays. At the last second of the video, a wind sound effect plays, reminding us that this is a smots gaming video.

In the middle of smots-8 the Batman intro (1966) plays, except the name bat man is replaced with smots gaming, Madeline west instead of Adam west, Final Goodbye instead of Robin's actor, the executive producer is Parrot Dash, it also stars "Wind Springs Hamilton" and Maddy Thorson EXOK Games. This episode is the end of smots-7 to the start of smots-9 shown in 21 slides, with each slide showing entities as red rectangles and foreground tiles as blue rectangles with a solid white background, while beeps of different frequencies play on each slide. This is a reference to Webdriver Torso, a youtube channel created by youtube to be used as a testing channel, who made hundreds of thousands of videos with slideshows showing slides about 1 second long each. Each slide consists of a solid white background overlapped by two solid color opaque rectangles, one red and the other blue. Both rectangles are randomly sized, shaped, and positioned on the slide. When the two overlap, the red rectangle always appears over the blue one, and on rare occasions, the red rectangle completely covers up the blue one.

This is smots-8, but played in a very strange way. Madeline dashes above the first spring instead of into it, and then barely grabs onto the next platform. After hitting the second spring it dashes left too early and does a cornerjump to save it. It hits the next 3 springs very late. Madeline uses all of her stamina climbing the floating block before the next spring. Instead of doing an upright to hit the next spring safely, Madeline does a right dash and lands on the left side of the block, before climbing the block and hitting the very right edge of the spring. The next spring is hit very early with an up-demo dash. Finally, Madeline dashes straight up right before the last two falling blocks. It does the first updash off of the first falling block like normal, but instead of holding right it holds left, and grabs onto the side of the second falling block, and the block falls leaving madeline stranded next to the spinners. It pauses the game to contemplate how to save the situation, then performs a "spinner climb" which is similar to a spinner stun except instead of phasing through the spinners, it climbs up them. This is not a vanilla tech. When it reaches smots-9, it dashes as low as possible on the pillar.
